                  <decoDesc>
                     <summary> The manuscript includes some crude headpieces and full-page
                        miniatures. The latter, executed by the same artist, are painted in a
                        regional variant of the <term key="PostGondarineStyle">Post-Gondarine
                           Style</term> and </summary>

                     <decoNote type="drawing" xml:id="d1">
                        <locus target="#1v"/>
                        <desc> An <ref type="authFile" corresp="AT1012Equestrian"/> miniature
                           showing <persName ref="PRS4585Georgeo"/> slaying the dragon. The saint
                           has a rayed have rayed <term key="halo"/> and thrusts his <term key="spear"/> with a <term key="cross"/> finial in the neck of a
                           dragon with a coiled tail, wings, and horns. </desc>
                     </decoNote>

                     <decoNote type="drawing" xml:id="d2">
                        <locus target="#2r"/>
                        <desc> A miniature of the <ref type="authFile" corresp="AT1031VirginAndChild"/>, which follows the iconoraphy of the
                              <term key="saluspopuli"/>. <persName ref="PRS5684JesusCh"/> performs a
                              <term key="gestureblessing"/> blessing gesture with his right and
                           holds a <term key="codex"/> with his left hand. He and the <persName ref="PRS6819Mary"/> have rayed <term key="halo">halos</term>. Two
                              <term key="angel">angels</term> stand behind them holding up a canopy.
                        </desc>
                     </decoNote>

                     <decoNote type="drawing" xml:id="d3">
                        <locus target="#2v"/>
                        <desc> The <ref type="authFile" corresp="AT1005Crucifixion"/> miniature
                           features the <term key="deadjesus">Dead Jesus</term>. The <term key="beardless"/>
                           <persName ref="PRS5684JesusCh"/> is fastened by three nails to the <term key="cross"/>, wears a loincloth, has a rayed <term key="halo"/>. The
                              <persName ref="PRS6819Mary">Virgin Mary</persName>, to the right has
                           tears flowing down her cheeks and a rayed <term key="halo"/>. To the left
                           Longinus, depicted on a horse and with a pointed hat, pierces the right
                           side of Jesus with a <term key="spear"/>. The background, left unpainted,
                           features stars, and the <term key="sunandmoon"/>. </desc>
                     </decoNote>

                     <decoNote type="frame" xml:id="d4">
                        <locus target="#3r">3r</locus> (incipit of Text I): elaborate, coloured
                        (red, yellow) ornamental band; floral motifs, interlaces.</decoNote>

                     <decoNote type="frame" xml:id="d5">
                        <locus target="#34ra">34ra</locus>b (incipit of Text I-3): two simple,
                        coloured (red, black) ornamental bands; interlaces.</decoNote>


